Nr has both positive and negative impacts on the SDGs, with countries facing varying challenges based on their development stages. Low-income African countries should prioritize harnessing Nr's positive role in agricultural production and food supply to achieve SDG 1 and SDG 2 (Figs. 3
                     , 4
                     ). In contrast, emerging economies that have largely overcome poverty and hunger must be cautious about the adverse effects of Nr on achieving SDGs (Figs. 3, 4).
